{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d1b6e143-e2c3-464d-9dee-b71fc79fce46","content":"Here's what I found:\n\n**`my_app/views.py`, line 3** — `datetime.now()`\n\n```python\nnow = datetime.now()\n```\n\nThis is a **static call** embedded directly in the view, making it hard to test because you can't control the returned time.\n\n### Recommended fix\n\nInject the clock as a dependency so tests can substitute it:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request, clock=timezone.now):\n    now = clock()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nOr, in tests, use `unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nwith patch('my_app.views.datetime') as mock_dt:\n    mock_dt.now.return_value = datetime(2026, 1, 1)\n    response = index(request)\n```\n\n**Summary:** Only **1 untestable static** found — `datetime.now()` in `views.py:3`. The project is small, so the fix is straightforward. Want me to apply either approach?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a643c2e5-d5c9-4cd6-83a6-020809168eca","outputTokens":265,"requestId":"E3C6:39929D:B82DB9:D27975:6A053D57"},"id":"5586ffd5-12e0-4a31-906e-3b57ff598d95","timestamp":"2026-05-14T03:11:26.273Z","parentId":"a900d95d-2f51-4438-9b94-d4bfe779e84e"}
